(These are the reasons why the ALMIGHTY does not listen or hear our prayers):


***(1 John 5:14): And this is the confidence that we have in him, that, if we ask any thing according to his will, he heareth us:


***(Psalms 145:19): He fulfills the desires of those who fear Him; He hears their cry and saves them.


***(James 4:3): And when you do ask, you do not receive, because you ask with wrong motives, that you may squander it on your pleasures.


***(1 John 3:22): and we will receive from Him whatever we ask, because we keep His commandments and do what is pleasing in His sight.


***(Isaiah 59:1-2): Behold, the LORD'S hand is not shortened, that it cannot save; neither his ear heavy, that it cannot hear: But your iniquities have separated between you and your God, and your sins have hid his face from you, that he will not hear.


***(Psalms 66:18): If I regard iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear me: (Iniquity): Among the things that can block effective prayer is ongoing sin in a believer’s life).


***(James 4:6): But he giveth more grace. Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the proud, but giveth grace unto the humble.


***(Jeremiah 29:12-14): For I know the thoughts that I think toward you, says the Lord, thoughts of peace and not of evil, to give you a future and a hope. Then you will call upon Me and go and pray to Me, and I will listen to you. And you will seek Me and find Me, when you search for Me with all your heart. I will be found by you, says the Lord, and I will bring you back from your captivity;


***(Psalms 34:17): The righteous cry, and the LORD heareth, and delivereth them out of all their troubles.


***(John 5:16): The effectual fervent prayer of a righteous man availeth much.


***(Proverbs 15:29): The Lord is far from the wicked,
But He hears the prayer of the righteous.
